OL,3,C'Oldest' Post Office scandal victim
OL,4,Creceives government compensation
OL,6,FA woman believed to be the oldest
OL,7,Fvictim of the Post Office scandal has
OL,8,Fhad her compensation claim settled by
OL,9,Fthe government.
OL,11,FBetty Brown, 92, ran the Annfield
OL,12,FPlain Post Office near Stanley in
OL,13,FCounty Durham with her late husband
OL,14,FOswall in the 1990s and early 2000s.
OL,16,FThey spent tens of thousands of pounds
OL,17,Fto plug gaps in their accounts which
OL,18,Fwere created by the faulty Horizon
OL,19,Fsoftware that made it look like money
OL,20,Fwas missing from their Post Office
OL,21,Fbranch.
