OL,3,C'Oldest' Post Office scandal victim
OL,4,Creceives government compensation
OL,6,FMany subpostmasters are believed to
OL,7,Fstill be awaiting full compensation,
OL,8,Fdespite the previous government
OL,9,Fannouncing payouts of up to #600,000
OL,10,Ffor those with overturned convictions.
OL,12,FPost Office Minister Blair McDougall
OL,13,Fsaid: "Betty has been a fierce
OL,14,Fadvocate for postmasters and this
OL,15,FGovernment has now paid out over #1.2
OL,16,Fbillion to more than 9000 victims. We
OL,17,Fcan confirm that Betty's claim has
OL,18,Freached the end of the scheme process
OL,19,Fand been settled."
